{{distinguish|Microsoft Money}} {{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Products|date=June 2010}} {{self-published|date=June 2010}} {{refimprove|date=June 2010}} {{primary sources|date=June 2010}} }} {{Infobox software | name = Money | developer = Jumsoft | latest_release_version = 4.4 | latest_release_date = {{release date|2012|12|12}} | operating_system = [[macOS|Mac OS X]] | genre = [[Personal finance]] | website = http://www.jumsoft.com/money/ }}
'''Money''' is a [[personal finance]] management tool for [[macOS|Mac OS X]] by Jumsoft. The latest major release, version 3.0, was released in 2008. Money is designed for [[accounting]] and [[budget]]ing as well as for creating [[inventory]] lists and [[invoice]]s, and is primarily marketed to [[small business]] and home users. The application is also used for [[investment management]], as it offers a Portfolio feature displaying [[share (finance)|share]] information, security quote history, [[stock market index|market indices]], and the market value of a user’s share [[portfolio (finance)|portfolio]]. Money does not support the traditional [[double-entry bookkeeping system|double-entry accounting]] and is based on separate cash, bank, investment, and other accounts.<ref>[http://www.jumsoft.com/money/ Money official site], visited June 9, 2010</ref>
Money is a part of Jumsoft’s Home Business Trio bundle of business management applications.<ref>[http://www.jumsoft.com/businesstrio/ Home Business Trio description] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528151851/http://www.jumsoft.com/businesstrio/ |date=2010-05-28 }}, visited June 9, 2010</ref> Versions for [[iPhone]]<ref>[http://dailyappshow.com/jumsoft-releases-money-1-0-for-iphone-small-business-accounting Jumsoft Releases Money 1.0 for iPhone], visited June 9, 2010</ref> and [[iPad]]<ref>[http://www.macworld.com/article/150777/2010/04/jumsoft_ipad.html Jumsoft Money updated with iPad compatibility]</ref> are available for free at [[iTunes Store]].
==History== The first version of Money was released in 2003<ref>[http://www.versiontracker.com/dyn/moreinfo/macosx/21766&vid=125536&mode=info Money 1.0 release notes on Version Tracker]{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, visited June 9, 2010</ref> and contained very basic tools for entering [[financial transaction]]s and performing analysis. It was designed for [[Mac OS X 10.2]] and [[Mac OS X v10.3|10.3]], and was mainly intended for the [[United States|U.S.]] market. In 2006, Money 2 [[beta version|Beta]] was launched, featuring a substantially expanded range of functions. The new version introduced budgeting, visual reports, scheduled transactions and transfers among accounts, as well as multiple [[currency|currencies]]. Less than a month after the beta version appeared, Jumsoft released a stable version 2.0. Version 3.0 was launched in 2008 and added budget and investment portfolio monitoring, inventories, and invoices to the list of features.
